The paper discusses machine learning techniques for analyzing and visualizing high-dimensional data, which is a common topic in several sub-categories of computer science. However, the use of interactive similarity projections and end-to-end trainable architecture suggests that the paper is most likely to belong to the sub-category of Machine Learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper evaluates the proposed framework on image and text datasets, which are commonly studied in Computer Vision (cs.CV) and Natural Language Processing (cs.CL) sub-categories, respectively. The paper also mentions the use of neural embeddings, which is a topic in Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Information Retrieval (cs.IR) sub-categories. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories for this paper are cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.CL, and cs.IR, in that order.
